resource.purpose: The purpose of this is to test the system to make sure we have complete end-to-end functionality
resource.usage: This is to be used in conjunction with a patient-facing FHIR application.

action.title: BP is normal
action.description: Determines if the patient has normal BP (systolic < 120 AND diastolic < 80)

documentation.display: Info for those with normal blood pressure

action.description: Do something else, or nothing at all

action.title: BP is elevated
action.description: Determines if the patient has elevated BP (systolic 120-129 AND diastolic < 80)

documentation.display: Info for those with elevated blood pressure

action.description: Do something else, or nothing at all

action.title: Determine if patient has stage 1 hypertension
action.description: This action identifies a patient who has stage 1 hypertension (systolic 130-139 OR diastolic 80-89).

documentation.display: Info for those with stage 1 hypertension

action.description: Do something else, or nothing at all

action.title: Determine if patient has stage 2 hypertension
action.description: This action identifies a patient who has stage 2 hypertension (systolic >= 140 OR diastolic >= 90).

documentation.display: Info for those with stage 2 hypertension

action.description: Do something else, or nothing at all

action.title: Determine if patient is in a hypertension crisis
action.description: This action identifies a patient who is in a full-blown hypertension crisis (systolic > 180 AND/OR diastolic > 120).

documentation.display: Info for those with hypertension crisis

action.description: Do something else, or nothing at all
